$ Normal.dotm

`Normal.dotm` (typically located in →> Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData/Roaming/Microsoft/Templates[`%APPDATA%\Microsoft\Templates`]) I is the default Word template that is automatically opened when → Microsoft/Office/Word is started.
This template can be used to define default → design/font/font[fonts], styles, margins, spacing for new Word documents.

In order to use a different default template when Word is started, the `/t` command line can be used. This command line option must not be seperated with a space from the file name: `/tc:\users\rene\other.dotm`.

sa:
  → Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData/Roaming/Microsoft/Templates[`%PROGRAMFILES%\Microsoft Office\root\Templates`]
